THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
commemorate the celebration of St. Patrick's Day and recognizes the cultural and historic
links between Ireland and Louisiana and the establishment of the American Irish State
Legislators Caucus.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
National Co-chairs of the American Irish State Legislators Caucus: Senator Beth Mizell of
Louisiana; Senator Mark Daly, Chair of the Senate of Ireland; Representative Brian Patrick
Kennedy of Rhode Island; Speaker Robin Vos of Wisconsin; Assemblywoman Carol
Murphy of New Jersey; Senator Shannon O'Brien of Montana; Representative Killian
Timoney of Kentucky; Representative Fran Hurley of Illinois; Representative James
Gallagher of California; Senator Ogden Driskill of Wyoming; Senator Wayne Harper of
Utah; Representative Bridget Walsh Moore of Missouri; Representative Maureen Terry of
Maine; Representative John Lawn of Massachusetts; Delegate Roger Hanshaw of West
Virginia; Representative Marcus Evans Jr. of Illinois; and Representative Mia Costello of
Alaska.
